[[File:Bengal United Service Club.jpg|right|thumb|Bengal United Service Club, c. 1905]]

'''The Bengal Club''' is a [[Gentlemen's club|social club]] in [[Kolkata]], [[West Bengal]]. It was opened in 1827 as the ''Calcutta United Service Club''. The club's first President was Lt. Col. The Hon. J. Finch. The club-house was in a building in [[Esplanade, Kolkata|Esplanade]] West, erected in 1813 and has been catering elites since 1827.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.news-herald.com/article/HR/20180114/ENTERTAINMENT/180119765|title=India: Strolling through Kolkata’s colonial past|access-date=2018-01-17|language=en}}</ref> The club has a dining hall, a number of bars, [[libraries]] and a gymnasium and is built in the colonial style. Members are also able to visit other reciprocal clubs around [[India]], as well as many parts of the world. The Club has strict dress regulations. This Club is one of the most prestigious clubs in Calcutta. It serves the tradition of Bengal and British culture with a blend of ethics and vision to rule in the heart of culture.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiawest.com/news/india/strolling-through-kolkata-s-colonial-past/article_e7e10418-f7f2-11e7-bb11-b3e0388b3a87.html|title=Strolling Through Kolkata’s Colonial Past|last=AP|first=DENIS D. GRAY,|work=India West|access-date=2018-01-17|language=en}}</ref>

In 2018, the club was featured in the Top 100 Platinum City Clubs in an election conducted by Club Leaders Forum.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://clubleadersforum.com/pcow/platinum-clubs-2018-city/|title=Top 100 Platinum City Clubs of the World 2018-19 – Platinum Clubs of the World|website=clubleadersforum.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-17}}</ref>

