{{infobox ethnic group| |group=Bichaghchi |image= |population= Unknown |popplace=[[Kerman Province]], [[Iran]] |rels=[[Shia Islam]] |langs=[[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]] and [[Persian language|Persian]] |related-c=[[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijanis]] and other [[Turkic people]]s }} '''Bichaghchis''' or '''Bichaghchi people''', ({{lang-fa|مردم بچاقچی}}) are a [[Turkic people|Turkic]] sub-ethnic group of [[Iranian Turks|Turks in Iran]], mainly living in [[Kerman Province]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cgie.org.ir/shavad.asp?id=123&avaid=6417 |title=جبال بارزی، بچاقچی |publisher=World Islamic Encyclopedia |date= |accessdate=7 May 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706122424/http://www.cgie.org.ir/shavad.asp?id=123&avaid=6417 |archivedate=6 July 2012 |df= }}</ref> The Bichaghchis are predominantly Shi'a Muslim and speak [[Azerbaijani language]] and [[Persian language]].
