{{Infobox language |name=Bitama |nativename= |states=[[Eritrea]], [[Ethiopia]] |region= |ethnicity=[[Kunama people]] |speakers=? |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Kunama languages|Kunama]] |iso3=none |iso3comment=(included in {{ethnolink|kun}}) |glotto=bita1252 |glottorefname=Bitama }}
'''Bitama''' (Bitaama) is a divergent variety of [[Kunama languages|Kunama]] that is [[mutually unintelligible]] enough to be considered a distinct language. It is spoken by the [[Kunama people]] who straddle the western [[Eritrea]]n–[[Ethiopia]]n border.
