The '''Boazi languages''' are a pair of languages in the [[Trans–New Guinea]] family. They were previously classified in the [[Marind languages|Marind]] branch.

The languages are [[Kuni-Boazi language|Kuni-Boazi]] and [[Zimakani language|Zimakani]].

