The '''Duna–Pogaya languages''' are a proposed small [[language family|family]] of [[Trans–New Guinea languages]] in the classification of Voorhoeve (1975) and [[Malcolm Ross (linguist)|Ross]] (2005). However, connections between the two languages, [[Duna language|Duna]] and [[Bogaya language|Bogaya]], are tenuous, and proposed connections to the larger [[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] family are not convincing.<ref>{{glottolog|boga1247|Bogaya}}</ref>

