'''Kinare''' is a name given to one of the sub-tribes of the [[Ogiek]] community which is found within [[Kenya]]. The original name is Akiek pa Kinare. They generally spoke a [[Kalenjin languages|Kalenjin]] dialect. A pre-colonial [[Kikuyu people|Kikuyu]] leader by the name of [[Waiyaki Wa Hinga]] had some roots in this community which has led to many theories being created about him being a [[Kalenjin people|Kalenjin]] and not a Kikuyu.{{cn|date=March 2017}}

